9. Troubleshooting — Migration & Post-Migration

Issue	Likely Cause	Resolution
VM BSOD on boot (Windows)	VirtIO storage driver missing	Boot from WinPE ISO in Prism; inject VirtIO drivers from Nutanix VirtIO ISO; reboot
Linux kernel panic on boot	initramfs missing VirtIO modules	Boot from rescue ISO; chroot; run dracut -f --regenerate-all; rebuild initrd
VM boots but no network (no IP)	NIC not mapped / VirtIO NIC driver missing	In Prism, verify NIC mapping; in VM, check 'ip link' — if NIC missing, install virtio-net
IP conflict after migration	Source VM still powered on / DHCP not updated	Confirm source VM is OFF; update DHCP reservation MAC address to new NC2 VM MAC
DNS not resolving for migrated VM	DNS A record still points to old IP	Update DNS A and PTR records; verify DNS propagation with nslookup from multiple clients
Domain join broken after migration	Machine account password expired or MAC changed	Run: netdom resetpwd; or disjoin/rejoin domain in a maintenance window
Application cannot connect to DB	Firewall rule references old IP	Update security group / firewall rules with new NC2 VM IP
Backup job failing on NC2 VM	Backup agent not running / old host config	Reinstall or reconfigure backup agent; update backup server with new VM IP/credentials
High I/O latency post-migration	Data on cold HDD tier (ILM not warmed up)	Wait 15–30 mins for Nutanix ILM to promote data to SSD; check storage tier activity in Prism
Monitoring agent not reporting metrics	Agent using old IP as report destination	Reconfigure monitoring agent with correct server IP; restart agent service
Cutover fails with 'disk conversion error'	AHV incompatible disk type (e.g., RDM)	Remove RDM from migration scope; migrate RDM data separately; attach to target VM post-migration

